Phase Flow [HIGH LEVEL]
---
1: Foundation & Planning
2: Architecture & System Design
3: Core Infrastructure Setup
4: Backend Development (Feature Modules)
5: Frontend Development (Feature Modules)
6: Integration (Frontend ↔ Backend)
7: Analytics & Intelligence Layer
8: PWA Enablement
9: Testing & QA
10: Deployment (SQLite-based)
11: Post-Deployment Iteration
===
1. Foundation & Planning
    1.1 Product Definition: Product Requirements Document (PRD)
        1.1.1 Define core app vision
            1.1.1.1 Write product vision statement
            1.1.1.2 Define problem statement
            1.1.1.3 Define value proposition
            1.1.1.4 Define key differentiators (why Theria isn’t just another finance app)
        1.1.2 Identify target users
            1.1.2.1 Define primary user personas (e.g., student, working individual)
            1.1.2.2 Define user goals per persona
            1.1.2.3 Define pain points
            1.1.2.4 Define usage scenarios
        1.1.3 Define MVP scope
            1.1.3.1 List all features (you already have this)
            1.1.3.2 Classify features:
                - Core (must-have)
                - Supporting
                - Future
            1.1.3.3 Define feature boundaries (what’s intentionally NOT included)
            1.1.3.4 Define acceptance criteria per core feature
        1.1.4 Define success metrics
            1.1.4.1 Define activation metrics (first transaction created, etc.)
            1.1.4.2 Define engagement metrics (daily usage, streaks)
            1.1.4.3 Define retention metrics
            1.1.4.4 Define system KPIs (performance, response time)
    1.2 Feature Breakdown
        1.2.1 Records (transactions)
        1.2.2 Streams (income/expense flows)
        1.2.3 Budgeting
        1.2.4 Savings goals
        1.2.5 Categories
        1.2.6 Accounts
        1.2.7 Streaks
        1.2.8 Notifications
        1.2.9 Analytics
    1.3 Agile Planning
        1.3.1 Create product backlog
        1.3.2 Define epics per feature
        1.3.3 Break epics into user stories
        1.3.4 Define sprint cycles (1–2 weeks)
        1.3.5 Define definition of done (DoD)
2. Architecture & System Design
    2.1 Backend Architecture
        2.1.1 Define modular monolith boundaries
        2.1.2 Define service–repository contracts
        2.1.3 Define module communication rules
    2.2 Database Design
        2.2.1 Identify entities
        2.2.2 Design ERD
        2.2.3 Define relationships
        2.2.4 Normalize schema
        2.2.5 Plan migrations
    2.3 API Design
        2.3.1 Define REST endpoints
        2.3.2 Define request/response schemas
        2.3.3 Define error handling structure
        2.3.4 Authentication strategy (JWT/session)
    2.4 Frontend Architecture
        2.4.1 Define feature-based structure
        2.4.2 Define global state strategy
        2.4.3 Define routing structure
        2.4.4 Define API client abstraction
3. Core Infrastructure Setup
    3.1 Repository Setup
        3.1.1 Initialize monorepo structure
        3.1.2 Setup git workflows
    3.2 Backend Setup (Django)
        3.2.1 Initialize Django project
        3.2.2 Configure SQLite
        3.2.3 Setup core modules
        3.2.4 Setup base classes (controller/service/repo)
        3.2.5 Setup authentication utilities
    3.3 Frontend Setup (React)
        3.3.1 Initialize React app (Vite/CRA)
        3.3.2 Setup TypeScript
        3.3.3 Setup routing
        3.3.4 Setup global state
        3.3.5 Setup API client
    3.4 Dev Environment
        3.4.1 Environment variables
        3.4.2 Linting & formatting
        3.4.3 Basic CI (optional early)
4. Backend Development (Modules)
    4.1 Authentication Module
        4.1.1 User model
        4.1.2 Registration
        4.1.3 Login
        4.1.4 Token/session handling
        4.1.5 Middleware/guards
    4.2 Account Management
        4.2.1 Account model
        4.2.2 CRUD operations
        4.2.3 Balance tracking
    4.3 Categories
        4.3.1 Category model
        4.3.2 Default categories
        4.3.3 Custom categories
    4.4 Records (Transactions)
        4.4.1 Record model
        4.4.2 Create/edit/delete records
        4.4.3 Link to accounts & categories
    4.5 Streams (Income/Expense)
        4.5.1 Recurring logic
        4.5.2 Scheduling system
        4.5.3 Execution engine
    4.6 Budget Module
        4.6.1 Budget model
        4.6.2 Budget allocation logic
        4.6.3 Threshold alerts
    4.7 Savings Module
        4.7.1 Savings goals
        4.7.2 Progress tracking
    4.8 Streaks Module
        4.8.1 Streak logic
        4.8.2 Daily/weekly tracking
        4.8.3 Reward triggers
    4.9 Notifications Module
        4.9.1 Notification model
        4.9.2 Trigger system
        4.9.3 Delivery logic (in-app)
    4.10 Analytics Module
        4.10.1 Aggregation queries
        4.10.2 Financial summaries
        4.10.3 Trend calculations
